
[1]microcosm

   MIC'ROCOSM, n. [Gr. small, and world.] Literally, the little world; but
   used for man, supposed to be an epitome of the universe or great world.

   Microcosmic salt,a triple salt of soda, ammonia and phosphoric acid,
   obtained from urine.
